Weyden and Nola Peceur accumulated 47 points to win a golf challenge played at the Polokwane Golf Club on Saturday. In second place were Adam Milanzi and former Polokwane Executive Mayor Freddy Greaver on 46 points. Jan Nel and Raymond Mushaike occupied the third position as they finished with 45 points on a count in. Nola claimed yet another prize after playing nearest to pin eight while Thabo Shingange ascended the stage to collect a prize for playing the longest drive at pin number two. Peter Ascenco made the jackpot draw at holes 2, 7, 9 and 12 but none of the golfers were fortunate enough to win the draw. The jackpot was standing at 2 840 units while 2 272 units was payable. Story and photos: ENDY SENYATSI &gt;&gt;endy@observer.co.za Peter Masehela in action. Morne Myburgh putting. Aaron Seswapa aims to sink the ball.